title: Mikie Sherrill
added: When she took office in January 2019, Sherrill became the first Democrat to hold the seat since 16-term incumbent [[Joseph Minish]] was defeated in 1984 after the district was redrawn to be more Republican.<ref>{{cite news|last1=NARVAEZ|first1=ALFONSO A.|title=MINISH CONSIDERS CAUSES OF HIS LOSS|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1984/11/11/nyregion/minish-considers-causes-of-his-loss.html|access-date=6 March 2016|work=The New York Times|date=11 November 1984}}</ref> She was the first Democrat since Minish's defeat to garner more than 40 percent of the vote in the district. Sherrill is the only elected Democrat above the county level in much of the western portion of the district—Frelinghuysen's former base. For instance, in the district's share of [[Morris County, New Jersey|Morris County]], which accounts for most of its population, all but one state senator and two state assemblymen are Republicans.
